headline: Is Costco Still a Buy at $1,000 per Share?
summary: In the retail sector, Costco (NASDAQ: COST) has been one of the biggest long-term winners.  A favorite of Warren Buffett's late partner, Charlie Munger, Costco's killer business model, low-price ethos, and consistent growth even in a tough retail environment have made for another winning year in 2024.  Make no mistake, Costco isn't a cheap stock.
